    "content": "<p>The decreasing order of nucleophilicity among the following nucleophiles is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5jckd9/cde88cac-5880-4f00-b403-fcb617f7a11a/579b3cd0-2544-11ef-967d-7bb8a1750de0/file-jaoe38c1lx5jckda.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5jckd9/cde88cac-5880-4f00-b403-fcb617f7a11a/579b3cd0-2544-11ef-967d-7bb8a1750de0/file-jaoe38c1lx5jckda.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 2 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "III, II, I, IV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "II, III, I, IV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "IV, III, II, I"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "I, II, III, IV"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>If acid is weak, its conjugate base (nucleophile) is strong and vice-versa.</p>\n<p>I. <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5ju5za/58db3796-35a4-4494-8975-ef3761e19fa0/410e7660-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5ju5zb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5ju5za/58db3796-35a4-4494-8975-ef3761e19fa0/410e7660-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5ju5zb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 2 English Explanation 1\"> is conjugate base of <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5julad/508355e6-a03e-4619-9022-01091e293e56/4ce1a750-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5julae.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5julad/508355e6-a03e-4619-9022-01091e293e56/4ce1a750-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5julae.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>II. CH$$_3$$O$$^-$$ is a conjugate base of CH$$_3$$OH</p>\n<p>III. CN$$^-$$ is a conjugate base of HCN</p>\n<p>IV. <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5jvrpt/b5f21cb9-6182-4f83-9e1d-e06b35ea387d/6da82810-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5jvrpu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5jvrpt/b5f21cb9-6182-4f83-9e1d-e06b35ea387d/6da82810-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5jvrpu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 2 English Explanation 3\"> is a conjugate base of <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5jwee1/3864e057-475b-4ff8-8484-d729f21764b6/7f2bcc90-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5jwee2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5jwee1/3864e057-475b-4ff8-8484-d729f21764b6/7f2bcc90-2546-11ef-be66-917bd4c47278/file-jaoe38c1lx5jwee2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 2 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p>Order of acidic nature is IV &gt; I &gt; III &gt; II.</p>\n<p>So, nucleophilicity order is II &gt; III &gt; I &gt; IV.</p>",
