    "explanation": "<p>In option (c), the hydrogen of $$-$$CH group is\n<br><br> surrounded by three <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ls2j1d2c/2036b9a4-59e9-4aa5-b7c0-6b2ad8c7b6c6/b138d950-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j1d2d.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ls2j1d2c/2036b9a4-59e9-4aa5-b7c0-6b2ad8c7b6c6/b138d950-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j1d2d.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: inline-block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 15vh;vertical-align: middle\" alt=\"BITSAT 2020 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 4 English Explanation 1\"> groups as:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ls2j00z0/a03eefd1-270f-4d41-8eb3-9cd0b72c7810/8c1232c0-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j00z1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ls2j00z0/a03eefd1-270f-4d41-8eb3-9cd0b72c7810/8c1232c0-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j00z1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2020 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 4 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Here, O of CO attracts, the electron density towards itself. Thus, (c) has most acidic hydrogen among given compounds.</p>\n<p>Or</p>\n<p>The anion formed after removal of<br><br> acidic proton in<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1ls2j3mub/34d22b42-6ec1-4de0-815d-5f18ce86e21f/f0646b30-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j3muc.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1ls2j3mub/34d22b42-6ec1-4de0-815d-5f18ce86e21f/f0646b30-c09f-11ee-82bd-719b984fd5c4/file-6y3zli1ls2j3muc.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: inline-block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 15vh;vertical-align: middle\" alt=\"BITSAT 2020 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 4 English Explanation 3\"> is stablised by $-R$-effect of three $\\mathrm{C}=\\mathrm{O}$ groups.</p>\n<p>Thus, (c) has most acidic hydrogen among given compounds.</p>",
